onship results (1990\u201399)#1995 Final results|1995 San Francisco]]| [[Soling]]}}\n| show-medals      = yes\n| updated          = \n}}\n\n'''David \"Dave\" Adams Curtis''' (born June 22, 1946 in [[Marblehead, Massachusetts]]) is an American sailor and sail maker <ref name=\"NSHoF\" /><ref name=\"EYC\" />. As a sailor he competed at the highest level in many National and International classes. Dave won five [[Soling North American Championship|North American]], four US, one European and one World Championship in the [[Soling]], <ref name=\"DCNSHoF\" /><ref name=\"TUFTS\" /><ref name=\"SolingGuide1996\" /><ref name=\"HEYC\" />. He also won many championships in the [[Etchells]] and other classes. As sail maker he held franchises for, among others, [[Horizon Sails]], [[North Sails]] and [[Doyle Sails]].\n\nCurtis was inducted into the [[National Sailing Hall of Fame]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nshof.org/inductees/curtis-dave/|title=Dave Adams Curtis 2013 Inductee |publisher=Nshof.org |date= |accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\nWikidata entity link: {{Wikidata entity link|Q80635362}}\n{{Footer American Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Footer North American Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer World Champions Soling}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n <ref name=NSHoF> {{cite web\n   |url                 = http://www.nshof.org/hall-of-fame/class-of-2013\n   |title               = Class of 2013\n   |publisher           = National Sailing Hall of Fame\n   |accessdate          = 30 Oct 2019\n  }}</ref>\n  <ref name             = DCNSHoF> {{cite web\n    | editor1-last      = Vaughan \n    | editor1-first     = Roger\n    | editor1-link      = Roger Vaughan (NSHOF)\n    | url               = http://www.nshof.org/hall-of-fame/class-of-2013/176-the-national-sailing-hall-of-fame/hall-of-fame-2013/795-curtis-david-2013-hall-of-fame\n    | title             = Curtis, Dave - 2013 Hall of Fame \n    | website           = www.nshof.org\n    | accessdate        = 30 October 